# scripts/ci/check-size-band-policy.known-violations
#
# Size-band policy baseline allow-list (PR-15.7 follow-up).
#
# Mirror of scripts/ci/check-loc-thresholds.sh KNOWN_VIOLATIONS_BASELINE
# pattern: every path listed here is a legacy file that already exceeds
# the 50 000-byte hard-fail boundary at the moment the gate was wired.
# Each entry surfaces as a GitHub Actions `::warning file=...` (auditable
# but NOT hard-failing) so reviewers see the carry-over in PR UI.
#
# ONE BLANK-OR-COMMENT LINE between entries is intentional: the regex
# `^[[:space:]]*$|^#` strips them so the comparison remains exact-match.
#
# SSOT discipline:
#   * Add an entry ONLY when (a) a new long-file legacy is grandfathered,
#     or (b) the README comment below is updated to log the addition with
#     a tracking-ref in `docs/metrics/loc-refactor-history.md`.
#   * Remove an entry ONLY when the file is refactored below 50 000 bytes
#     (or explicitly granted a `// size-benchmark: <band>` header).
#   * The companion file `scripts/ci/check-size-band-policy.sh` reads this
#     list at gate-time. If a new file appears with size > 50 000 bytes
#     without a `// size-benchmark:` header AND NOT listed here, the gate
#     emits `::error file=...` and exits 1.
#
# Update ONLY when:
#   (a) a previously-baselined file is refactored (delete the entry), or
#   (b) you explicitly accept a new long-file carry-over (append the
#       entry + add a tracking-ref in loc-refactor-history.md § 19).
#
